snippet: Women with a false-positive mammogram or breast biopsy result have an increased risk of breast cancer over the next 10 years compared with those with a true negative result, a new report has found.
abstract: Women with a false-positive mammogram or breast biopsy result have an increased risk of breast cancer over the next 10 years compared with those with a true negative result, a new report has found.

headline.main: False Positive Breast Tests Tied to Increased Cancer Risk
